results.name: a(n) = number of positive divisors, k, of n where d(k) divides d(n). (d(m) = number of positive divisors of m, A000005)
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 12 has 6 divisors (1,2,3,4,6,12). The number of divisors of each of these divisors of 12 form the sequence (1,2,2,3,4,6). Of these, five divide d(12)=6: 1,2,2,3,6. So a(12) = 5.
program: def a(n): return sum([1*(divisor_count(n)%divisor_count(d)==0) for d in divisors(n)]) # _Indranil Ghosh_, May 25 2017
